The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, July 18, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Sunday, July 18, 2004				 																Footlights 				 																																	Book your seats for Lights Out, directed by Jayant Kripalani, at GD Birla Sabhagar, 7 pm. Whose play is it				 																																	Tune in to views on the Loyalty of a director to the playwright at a seminar, organised as part of the Ganakrishti Natya Utsav 2004, at Sisir Mancha, 10 am. Jhumur (Bengali) and Singarevva and the Palace (English), will be staged at 3 pm and 6.30 pm respectively. Monsoon magic				 																																	Join in an adda over poetry, prose and music as the perfect Ode to a Rainwoman this monsoon, at Caf Coffee Day, Park Street, 6 .30 pm. Chalk the walk				 																																	Sort out your career moves at Career Plan 2004, a mega career fair, at Netaji Indoor Stadium. 
